{{Infobox writer <!-- For more information see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]]. --> | name = Ardian Vehbiu | image = Ardian Vehbiu.jpg | image_size = 220px | alt = Ardian Vehbiu in 2015 | caption = Vehbiu in 2015 | birth_date = 1959 | birth_place = [[Tirana]], [[Albania]] | occupation = Writer, Translator | language = Albanian, English, Italian and French | nationality = [[Albanian people|Albanian]] | website = {{URL|http://peizazhe.com}} }}
'''Ardian Vehbiu''' is an Albanian author and translator. He was born in [[Tirana]], [[Albania]] in 1959 and now resides in [[New York City]]. He is the author of 12 [[non-fiction]] and [[fiction|fiction books]], as well as of a number of research papers in [[linguistics]] and [[semiotics]].{{citation needed|date=November 2015}} He is the winner of the 2009 "Gjergj Fishta"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegrafi.com/magazina/cmimi-i-madh-i-letersise-per-agron-tufen-18-520.html|title=Çmimet Kombëtare Letrare 2009|accessdate=November 25, 2015}}</ref> national non-fiction award with "Shqipja totalitare", (2009), as well as the winner of the 2014 "Ardian Klosi"<ref>{{cite news|url=http://english.traduki.eu/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1654:ardian-klosi-preis-erstmals-in-tirana-verliehen&catid=292&Itemid=148|title=First Ardian Klosi Prize awarded in Tirana|accessdate=November 25, 2015}}</ref> non-fiction award, with "Sende që nxirrte deti", (2013).
His writing is featured regularly in the Albanian press and has been translated in [[Italian language|Italian]], English and [[Romanian language|Romanian]]. He has also translated several works from [[Albanian language|Albanian]] into Italian, as well as from Italian, [[French language|French]] and English into Albanian.
