{{Infobox language |name = Simalungun |nativename = Sahap Simalungun |states = Indonesia |region = Sumatra (northern) |ethnicity = Batak Simalungun |speakers = 1.2 million |date = 2000 |ref = e18 |familycolor= Austronesian |fam2 = [[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3 = [[Northwest Sumatran languages|Northwest Sumatran]] |fam4 = [[Batak languages|Batak]] |fam5 = Southern |iso3 = bts |glotto=bata1288 |glottorefname=Batak Simalungun |script = [[Latin script|Latin]], [[Batak script|Batak]] }}
'''Simalungun''', or '''Batak Simalungun''', is an [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian language]] of [[Sumatra]]. It is spoken mainly in [[Simalungun Regency]] and [[Pematang Siantar]], [[North Sumatra]], [[Indonesia]].
