'''Itanglese''', also known as '''Anglitaliano''' or (in the [[United Kingdom]]) '''Britalian''', is the [[Macaronic language|macaronic]] blend (at different degrees) of [[Italian language|Italian]] and [[English language|English]], in the speech of people who speak parts of the two languages, or whose primary language is different from that of the country where they live.

