{{Underlinked|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox scientist | name = Ken Hyland | image = File:Prof Ken Hyland.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1951|11|19|df=y}} | birth_place = | residence = | fields = {{plainlist | * [[Second language acquisition]] * [[Second language writing]] }} | workplaces = {{plainlist | * [[University of East Anglia]] }} | alma_mater = [[University of Warwick]] | doctoral_advisor = | thesis_title = Hedging in scientific research articles | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | known_for = {{plainlist | * [[Second language writing]] }} | author_abbrev_bot = | author_abbrev_zoo = | awards = | spouse = | children = | religion = | website = {{URL|https://people.uea.ac.uk/en/persons/k-hyland|Hyland on the website of the University of East Aanglia}} }}
'''Ken Hyland''' is Professor of Applied Linguistics in Education at the [[University of East Anglia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://caes.hku.hk/home/about-us/staff/khyland|title=Professor Ken Hyland page at CAES, HKU|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
Hyland is an applied linguist in the field of academic discourse, [[second language writing]] and English for Academic Purposes, and has published more than 26 books and 200 articles. Google Scholar shows him to be one of the most cited researchers in Applied Linguistics <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com.hk/citations?user=887HnVcAAAAJ&hl=en&oi=ao|title=Professor Ken Hyland page at Google Scholar|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
Along with [[Alister Cumming|Cumming]], [[Judit Kormos|Kormos]], [[Rosa Manchón|Manchón]], [[Paul Kei Matsuda|Matsuda]], [[Lourdes Ortega|Ortega]], [[Charlene Polio|Polio]], [[Neomy Storch|Storch]] and [[Marjolijn Verspoor|Verspoor]], Hyland is considered as one of the most prominent researchers on second language writing.
==Career== He is founding co-editor of the [[Journal of English for Academic Purposes]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.journals.elsevier.com/journal-of-english-for-academic-purposes/|title=Journal of English for Academic Purposes|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> and was co-editor of ''[[Applied Linguistics (journal)|Applied Linguistics]].''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://academic.oup.com/applij|title=Applied Linguistics|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
