'''Ridvan Dibra''' (born 9 January 1959) is an [[Albanian Literature|Albanian writer]].<ref>{{cite book|author1=Robert Elsie|authorlink1=Robert Elsie|title=Albanian Literature: A Short History|date=2005|publisher=I.B.Taurus|location=London|isbn=1-84511-031-5|page=190|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=ox3Wx1Nl_2MC&pg=PA190&dq=Ridvan+Dibra&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjqlcfui6vXAhWEy7wKHSaeDiIQ6AEINzAE#v=onepage&q=Ridvan%20Dibra&f=false}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Guraziu|first1=S.|title=Bisedë informale me krijues: Ridvan Dibra|journal=Ars Poetica|date=2009|issue=23|page=96|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=HRXxBQAAQBAJ&pg=PA96&dq=Ridvan+Dibra&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjqlcfui6vXAhWEy7wKHSaeDiIQ6AEIUTAJ#v=onepage&q=Ridvan%20Dibra&f=false|accessdate=8 November 2017|publisher=Lulu.com|language=Albanian|isbn=1304497828}}</ref> He was born in [[Shkodër]], Albania, where he graduated from university in Albanian Language and Literature and from 1994 started teaching the very same subject there. An innovative writer, Dibra is a leading figure of contemporary Albanian Literature.<ref>{{cite web|author=[[Robert Elsie]]|title=Ridvan DIBRA|url=http://www.albanianliterature.net/authors/modern/dibra/index.html|website=Robert Elsie:Albanian Literature|accessdate=2 November 2017}}</ref> He has been rewarded with several national and international prizes, including the ''Rexhai Surroi Prize'' for best novel of the year in Albanian speaking territories, for his 2012 novel, "''Legjenda e vetmisë''" (The Legend of Solitude).<ref name="albanianbooks2">{{cite web|url=http://www.albanianbooks.al/index.php/authors-2/ridvan-dibra/|title=Ridvan Dibra|website=AlbanianBooks|accessdate=2 November 2017}}</ref>
He has been called as one of the five greatest living Albanian writers.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Olluri|first1=Adil|title=Adil Olluri: A kemi Roman Postmodernë ?!|url=http://www.uet.edu.al/index.php/en/news/828-|website=UET (European University of Tirana)|accessdate=3 November 2017}}</ref>

